place.name: EDDRACHILLIS
place.gazetteerText: Eddrachillis, coast par., W. Sutherland, 135,555 ac., pop. 1525; the surface is very rugged, and is devoted chiefly to sheep-walks and deer-forest; Eddrachillis Bay, from Badcall (where the par. church is situated) to Drumbag, is studded with islets. (In 1887, John Bartholomew's Gazetteer of the British Isles)
